{
  "texts": [
    "The adoption of new LED volume technologies (Sect. 3.2.1) has delivered radical changes in canonical chroma-keying and automated roto-scoping (segmentation) practices, offering a new image-based paradigm for computer vision researchers.",
    "The ability to perform in-camera compositing and background VFX provides cinematographers with a tighter control over the end product, although equally presents new challenges such as color misalignment and optimal lighting set-ups. 4.",
    "Automated 3-D capture (Sect. 3.2.3 and 3.2.4) has delivered flexible new solutions to problems which were previously solved with sculpting/3-D modeling tools and/or hardware dependent photogrammetric methods.",
    "With the current push for compact, fast and accurate representations, it is likely that production-ready NeRFs and Gaussian Splats will become practical soon. 5.",
    "Human detection and pose estimation (Sect. 3.3.1) plays a large role in research tied to live broadcasting."
  ]
}